					<head>Pentateuch</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420" rend="visible">
						<summary>Pentateuch, Five Scrolls and Hafṭarot, provided with vowel-points, accents and masoretic notes.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420">
							<locus from="1r" to="259v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Torah, megilot ṿe-hafṭarot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תורה, מגילות והפטרות</title>
							<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
							<note>
								<p>This manuscript has a significant number of omissions in the text, supplied in the margin, chiefly by later hands.</p>
								<p>The whole book of Genesis is missing at the beginning of the manuscript.</p>
								<p>Some masoretic notes are written on folio 11r in the lower margin, on a piece of vellum with which the manuscript had been mended (originally belonging to another codex). Compare volume 2 of <ref target="Ginsburg_1880" type="page">334-345</ref>.</p>
							</note>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="46v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Exodus</title>
								<note>
									<p>Wanting chapters 1:1-6:22.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="46v" to="80r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Leviticus</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="80r" to="122r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Numbers</title>
								<note>
									<p>Wanting chapters 4:23-8:20</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="122r" to="166r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Deuteronomy</title>
								<note>
									<p>Folio 165v contains 2Chron. 24:5, 1Kings 8:27 and a numbers of single words and phrases from Genesis, chapters 19:16, 39:8, 19:6, 27:25 (v. 29) and Num. 32:42, all provided with vowel-points and accents in order to illustrate the use of accents and its names. Compare volume 1 of  <ref target="Ginsburg_1880" type="page">653</ref>.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="166r" to="175r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Esther</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="175r" to="178v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Song of Songs</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="178v" to="182v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Ruth</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="182v" to="187r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Lamentations</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="187r" to="195v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Ecclesiastes</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="195v" to="259v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Hafṭarot</title>
								<note>
									<p>Hafṭarot for Passover and Pentecost are accompanied with the pointed and accentuated Targum, starting on folio 224r.</p>
								</note>
								<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr">Hebrew, Aramaic</textLang>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of approximately the 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent rend="visible">259 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>305</height>
										<width>241</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>280</height>
										<width>188</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>259 folios (+3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end of the manuscript).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>32 extant quires, mostly of 8 leaves, with a lacuna after folio 85 and folio 243; also imperfect at the beginning and at the end.</p>
									<p>Quires are marked with catchwords on the last page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Some leaves had been damaged and were later restored; some of the leaves bear stains.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="23" writtenLines="23">
									<p>The main text is written in two columns, 23 lines a page.</p>
									<p>Lamentations and Ecclesiastes begin a new column; Numbers, Deuteronomy and Song of Songs begin a new leaf. All other books open a new page.</p>
									<p>In the Pentateuch the beginning of a new pericope is indicated by <quote>פפפ</quote> written within the column.</p>
									<p>The centre-marks indicating the middle verse and the middle letter in the Pentateuch are on folios 53r, 57r</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
